Using csvRedmine.hs
===================

One-time Setup
--------------

sudo apt-get install ghc cabal-install happy alex libz-dev
cabal update
cabal install wreq conduit cassava-conduit

Running
-------

Review your proposed changes, if you like::

  runghc csvRedmine.hs \
    -h https://clsp-redmine.cs.jhu.edu \
    -a $your_auth_token \
    -p $project_name \
    upsert -n < foo.csv

Commit your changes to the server:

  runghc csvRedmine.hs \
    -h https://clsp-redmine.cs.jhu.edu \
    -a $your_auth_token \
    -p $project_name \
    upsert -x < foo.csv

The ``-x`` indicates that we should clobber existing entries; leave it off if
you are just out to create new ones.
